Mid-life crisis happens to all of us. Normally it strikes working professional when they are around 35-40 yrs of age. It is a state where the person starts to think that he is currently handling or doing a job which is less challenging then the person's intellectual potential. 

Mid-life crisis comes with family problems also. Its the time when the family matters have been taken care and there is nothing to look forward. Post 7-10 years of marriage, with kids grown up enough to take care of themselves, sexual life taking a back seat, life seems so much less interesting. 

Mid-Life crisis is a phenomenon which is all in the mind.